The citation on Professor Yaa Asantewaa said I must develop a passion towards learning, to help me in everything I do and organise herself by helping the poor. I will also be very grateful for your help to reinterpret an ancient of Africans. To use art and culture so that it would reduce the poverty in the region. I am so proud to be an African. I am so proud of Professor Yaa Asantewaa.

So, women of Africa, with your generous heart you have passed a big test. Now let's go to Nairobi, Kenya to meet Sikiana Allan Kirwa. She's 15 years old. Together we will have to break a stigma again. I hope you will form a team of producers and directors and as well as actors and actresses Sikiana and her friends.

With the political and religious tension many of Sikiana's friends have left school. Monogamy is now the law in Kenya Republic. Women and children have been left with a lot of responsibilities.
